{{define "content"}}
<div class="config-sub" id="page-config-bot">
{{template "config_sub_header" $}}
<h1>Discord bot</h1>
<p class="sub">Install / re-authorize the bot and set the fallback guild. Per-project guilds live in each project’s settings.</p>

<div class="section card" id="bot-invite">
  <h2>Bot install / permission update URL</h2>
  <p class="sub" style="margin-top:0">
    Invite this bot or <strong>re-authorize</strong> it on a server already joined so the role picks up the current permission set.
    Required: View Channel, Send Messages, Manage Messages, <strong>Pin Messages</strong> (continuity brief card), Attach Files, Read Message History, Create Public Threads, Send Messages in Threads.
  </p>
  {{if .Config.InviteURL}}
  <div class="invite-row">
    <input id="invite-url" type="text" readonly value="{{.Config.InviteURL}}" onclick="this.select()">
    <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary" data-copy-target="invite-url">Copy</button>
    <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="{{.Config.InviteURL}}" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Open / re-authorize</a>
  </div>
  <p class="sub" style="margin:0.65rem 0 0">
    Client ID: <span class="mono">{{.Config.ClientID}}</span>
    · permissions <span class="mono">{{.Config.InvitePermissions}}</span>
    · scope <span class="mono">bot</span>
  </p>
  <p class="sub" style="margin:0.35rem 0 0">
    Changing the URL alone does not upgrade an already-joined bot — open the link above, pick the server, and approve again.
    Brief pin failures (<span class="mono">Missing Permissions</span> / code <span class="mono">50013</span>) mean <strong>Pin Messages</strong> is still missing on the bot role (Discord split this from Manage Messages).
  </p>
  <p class="sub" style="margin:0.35rem 0 0">Also enable <strong>Message Content Intent</strong> in the Developer Portal (Bot → Privileged Gateway Intents).</p>
  {{else}}
  <div class="flash err" style="margin:0">Could not build install URL{{if .Config.InviteError}}: {{.Config.InviteError}}{{end}}. Set a valid <span class="mono">discordToken</span> or <span class="mono">discordClientId</span> in config.json.</div>
  {{end}}
</div>

<div class="section card" id="default-guild">
  <h2>Default Discord guild (fallback)</h2>
  <p class="sub" style="margin-top:0">
    Used only when a project has no guild of its own. Prefer setting the guild on each project for multi-server setups.
  </p>
  <form class="inline" method="post" action="{{route "config.setGuild"}}" style="grid-template-columns: 1fr auto;">
    {{template "csrf" $}}
    <div>
      <label for="guild-id">Default guild ID</label>
      <input id="guild-id" type="text" name="discordGuildId" value="{{.Config.DiscordGuildID}}" placeholder="optional fallback" autocomplete="off">
    </div>
    <button type="submit">Save default guild</button>
  </form>
</div>
</div>
{{end}}
